I failed while trying to use Debian APT to install vm 7.19 (on Debian 4.0
at MPI), via these commands:

  # Debian vm package depends on emacs21.  Why isn't emacs22 acceptable?
  apt -yqq install vm
  cp -pR /usr/share/emacs/site-lisp/vm /usr/share/emacs/22.1/site-lisp/vm
  rm /usr/share/emacs/22.1/site-lisp/vm/vm.elc
  apt uninstall emacs21
  cp -pR /usr/share/emacs/22.1/site-lisp/vm /usr/share/emacs/site-lisp/vm

but at this point "vm-autoloads" was missing.
so I used the manual commands below.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

VM 7.19:

cd ~/emacs/emacs-22
wget ftp://ftp.uu.net/networking/mail/vm/vm-7.19.tar.gz
tar zxf vm-7.19.tar.gz
cd vm-7.19
make all
make INFODIR=/usr/share/info install-info
# Edit /usr/share/info/dir to add a line:
#   * VM: (vm).          			A mail reader.

===========================================================================
